Nutrition   
ğŸ Nutrition â€“ Between Preventive Potential and Realâ€‘World Barriers
Balanced nutrition has undeniable preventive potential: it protects against cardiovascular disease, diabetes, obesity, certain cancers, and even mental disorders. In theory, it deserves a major share in the prevention chart.

Yet the reality is harsh:

Nearly 40% of the global population cannot afford nutritious food.

Around 50% of adults are overweight or obese, trapped in unhealthy eating patterns.

